{{Infobox company | name = Akeed | logo = Akeed.png |founded = 2014 | homepage = [https://www.akeed.jo/index.php?option=com_aboutakeed&view=item&id=1&Itemid=102&lang=en] }}
'''The Jordanian Media Credibility Monitor "Akeed"''' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.akeed.jo/index.php?option=com_aboutakeed&view=item&id=1&Itemid=102&lang=en/The|title=عن المرصد|website=www.akeed.jo|language=ar-aa|access-date=2018-03-14}}</ref> is a tool that tracks the content of [[News media|media outlets]] in [[Jordan]]. It tracks the [[credibility]] of news material that is published and broadcast by Jordanian media outlets. It is one of the projects of the [[Jordan Media Institute]].<ref name="Jordan Media Institute">[http://www.jmi.edu.jo/en Jordan Media Institute]</ref>
Akeed was founded in 2014 with support from the King Abdullah Fund for Development<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kafd.jo/|title=KAFD Home - KAFD|publisher=|accessdate=24 November 2016}}</ref> as part of the Democratic Empowerment Programme. It is intended to holds Jordanian media outlets accountable, and to examine the credibility of news material that is published and broadcast. It also publishes periodic reports on the news.<ref>[http://www.akeed.ae/ Akeed]</ref>
