The principle of '''unicity''' explains that each event, each living being, each object, each person or each circumstance has the characteristic of its [[uniqueness]], of its particularity. Other similar events, living beings, objects, persons or circumstances may exist, but never the same entity.<ref>http://www.webdianoia.com/glosario/display.php?action=view&id=329&from=action=search%7Cby=U</ref>

